"Things change. Acknowledging what you need, when you need it is important. You’re never going to have it all all the time.” #FBWChat
“You get to decide what to change about yourself and how you grow. You get to say, ‘This is how I run my business.’” —@juliesygiel #FBWChat
“Recognize that you kick ass at work, and you could do that for your own thing if you wanted to,” @minalm tells female founders. #FBWChat
"If you keep thinking about all the alternatives and what you can fall back on, you won’t put your all into it.” —@minalm #FBWChat
“We’re all capable of doing so much. Let’s just get over that fear and get things done.” —@BelmaMc #FBWChat
“Women who are interested in supporting other women is key. They’re out there; you just need to find them.” —@erinebagwell #FBWChat

“It’s empowering to tell the stories that no one ever tells—not just the positive ones.” —@NicScoots of @WornCreative #FBWChat
“As founders, we all want to make an impact. How do you work to differentiate yourself?” asks @BelmaMc. #FBWChat
On building loyal customers: “People want to feel like more than just a number. They want to feel part of something.” —@juliesygiel #FBWChat
